No Rust changes in the fix commit. Let me check the Greptile comment about redundant `params.get()` — looking at the current code, the `display_name` parsing at line 195-199 uses a clean `match` pattern. The Greptile comment was about some other `params.get()` pattern. Let me check what it pointed to.

The Greptile comment said: "Redundant `params.get()` calls — can be simplified". Looking at the current code, I see `url` handling at lines 119-130 which still calls `params.get("url")` three times:

```rust
let url = if params.get("url").is_some() {
    if params.get("url").is_some_and(Value::is_null) {
        None
    } else {
        params
            .get("url")
            .and_then(|v| v.as_str())
            .map(|value| Secret::new(value.to_string()))
    }
} else {
    existing.and_then(|cfg| cfg.url.clone())
};
```

But that code predates this PR. Let me check whether the Greptile comment was about `display_name` specifically.

